It seems send_multipart() doesn't work when using flags with the asyncio loop due to incorrect arguments processing.

To reproduce use the example in [https://github.com/zeromq/pyzmq/blob/master/examples/asyncio/coroutines.py](url) line 47 from:

    yield from push.send_multipart([str(time.time() - tic).encode('ascii')])

to

    try:
        yield from push.send_multipart([str(time.time() - tic).encode('ascii')], flags=zmq.NOBLOCK)
    except zmq.error.Again:
        asyncio.sleep(0)

Seems to be related to zmq/eventloop/future.py: _add_send_event()

    def _add_send_event(self, kind, msg=None, kwargs=None, future=None):
        """Add a send event, returning the corresponding Future"""
        f = future or self._Future()
        if kind.startswith('send') and kwargs.get('flags', 0) & _zmq.DONTWAIT:
            # short-circuit non-blocking calls
            send = getattr(self._shadow_sock, kind)
            try:
                r = send(**kwargs)
            except Exception as e:
                f.set_exception(e)
            else:
                f.set_result(r)
            return f

        if hasattr(_zmq, 'SNDTIMEO'):
            timeout_ms = self._shadow_sock.sndtimeo
            if timeout_ms >= 0:
                self._add_timeout(f, timeout_ms * 1e-3)

        self._send_futures.append(
            _FutureEvent(f, kind, kwargs=kwargs, msg=msg)
        )
        if self.events & POLLOUT:
            # send immediately if we can
            self._handle_send()
        if self._send_futures:
            self._add_io_state(self._WRITE)
        return f

Possible fix (untested):

        if kind == 'send_multipart':
            kwargs['msg_parts'] = kwargs.pop('msg')

Regards,
Dorian

